{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"How to Preview and Test"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopreviewandtest"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"title":"How-to Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"],"anchor":"How-to-Guides","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformer that tracks a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"current","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" snapshot the way the real service reflects RevenueCat’s state: ","type":"text"},{"code":"send(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" updates it and pushes it through the stream, ","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfo()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"restorePurchases()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" return it, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" tears the stream down. Plug it into the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallPlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" you use in production. Drive entitlement transitions from your test or preview body.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the API reference, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Why a different mock from SwiduxPaywall’s","anchor":"Why-a-different-mock-from-SwiduxPaywalls","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" ships its own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" whose stream finishes after the initial yield. That works for static “Pro” and “Free” previews but cannot model purchase, refund, or family-share transitions as a sequence. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" keeps the stream open until you call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finish()"},{"type":"text","text":", which lets a single test verify the store reacts correctly to an "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"order"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of snapshots."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you only need a static state (one snapshot, one render pass), either mock works. When you need a sequence, use this one.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Step 1: Make the service injectable","anchor":"Step-1-Make-the-service-injectable","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Plumb the service through your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Store.configured()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" factory so previews and tests can override it:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension Store where State == AppState, Action == AppAction {","    static func configured(","        paywallService: any PaywallService = RevenueCatPaywallService(entitlementID: \"pro\")","    ) -> AppStore {","        let plugins = PluginHost<AppState, AppAction>()","        plugins.register(","            PaywallPlugin<AppState, AppAction>(","                state: \\.paywall,","                action: AppAction.paywall,","                extractAction: { if case .paywall(let a) = $0 { return a }; return nil },","                service: paywallService","            )","        )","        return Store(initialState: AppState(), reducer: AppReducer().reduce, plugins: plugins)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default keeps the live RevenueCat path for app launch. Previews and tests pass an override.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Step 2: Static previews — pick a state","anchor":"Step-2-Static-previews-pick-a-state","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the configured-state form when one snapshot is enough:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["#Preview(\"Free\") {","    let store = AppStore.configured(","        paywallService: MockRevenueCatPaywallService()","    )","    return ContentView().environment(store)","}","","#Preview(\"Pro\") {","    let store = AppStore.configured(","        paywallService: MockRevenueCatPaywallService(isPro: true)","    )","    return ContentView().environment(store)","}","","#Preview(\"Lifetime\") {","    let store = AppStore.configured(","        paywallService: MockRevenueCatPaywallService(hasPermanentLicense: true)","    )","    return ContentView().environment(store)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each preview gets its own store; the mock’s initial snapshot flows through ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" and updates the gate before the first render."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Step 3: Driving transitions in a test","anchor":"Step-3-Driving-transitions-in-a-test","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the test cares about a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"sequence","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of states — for example, the gate flipping from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" after a purchase — use the streaming form:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test(\"Store updates when entitlement transitions to pro\")","func storeReactsToProPurchase() async {","    let mock = MockRevenueCatPaywallService(isPro: false)","    let store = AppStore.configured(paywallService: mock)","","    store.send(.paywall(.observeCustomerInfo))","    await Task.yield()","    #expect(store.paywall.isPro == false)","","    mock.send(EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: true))","    await Task.yield()","    #expect(store.paywall.isPro)","","    mock.finish()","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"send(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" makes the snapshot current and pushes it through the active stream subscriber, which in this case is the plugin’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" effect. The store’s reducer applies "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".customerInfoUpdated"},{"type":"text","text":", the observer tree fires for changed properties, and the assertion sees the new value. Because "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":" also returns the sent snapshot, the refresh the plugin dispatches when the paywall is dismissed sees the purchased state too — the gate never regresses to the init-time value mid-test."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfoStream()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" replaces its continuation on every call. If your test requests the stream more than once (rare — ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" is dispatched once), the previous stream finishes — its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"for await"},{"type":"text","text":" loop terminates instead of hanging — and only the most recent subscriber receives "},{"code":"send(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" updates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"text":"Step 4: Driving transitions in a preview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-4-Driving-transitions-in-a-preview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Previews can drive transitions too — useful for verifying paywall sheet copy across states without running the app:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["#Preview(\"Purchase flow\") {","    let mock = MockRevenueCatPaywallService(isPro: false)","    let store = AppStore.configured(paywallService: mock)","","    return ContentView()","        .environment(store)","        .task {","            store.send(.paywall(.observeCustomerInfo))","            try? await Task.sleep(for: .seconds(2))","            mock.send(EntitlementSnapshot(isPro: true))","        }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The preview starts in the free state, runs the gated UI for two seconds, then transitions to pro — letting you eyeball both copy paths in one preview pane."}]},{"text":"Step 5: Simulating failures","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-5-Simulating-failures"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfoError"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restoreError"},{"type":"text","text":" to make the corresponding call throw — the plugin dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed"},{"type":"text","text":", sets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.error"},{"type":"text","text":", and your retry UI becomes testable:"}]},{"code":["@Test(\"Refresh failure surfaces an error the UI can retry from\")","func refreshFailureSurfacesError() async {","    struct Offline: Error {}","    let mock = MockRevenueCatPaywallService(isPro: false)","    let store = AppStore.configured(paywallService: mock)","","    mock.customerInfoError = Offline()","    store.send(.paywall(.refreshCustomerInfo))","    await Task.yield()","    #expect(store.paywall.error != nil)","","    mock.customerInfoError = nil","    store.send(.paywall(.refreshCustomerInfo))","    await Task.yield()","    #expect(store.paywall.error == nil)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The same hooks exercise ","type":"text"},{"code":"ResilientPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s last-known-good fallback: wrap the mock, make ","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfo()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" throw, and assert the cached entitlement holds.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Step 6: Tear the stream down","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-6-Tear-the-stream-down"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end of a test to terminate the stream cleanly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["mock.finish()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This causes any pending "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"for await … in stream"},{"type":"text","text":" to exit. Without it, the consuming "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":" may stay alive until the test runner reaps it. Tests that own the mock for their full duration can skip this — Swift Testing tears down the task tree when the test exits — but it’s a clean habit."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPreviewAndTest","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Drive entitlement state from SwiftUI previews and tests with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" — no RevenueCat SDK call required."}],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with "},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for drop-in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"text":" presentation.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToImplementService":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoimplementservice","title":"How to Implement the Service","abstract":[{"text":"Wire ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" into the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" plugin so the store sees real-time entitlement updates from RevenueCat."}],"role":"article"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/MockServiceReference":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/mockservicereference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","title":"Mock Service Reference","abstract":[{"text":"API reference for ","type":"text"},{"code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — a controllable "},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformer for previews and tests that does not touch ","type":"text"},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToAddAPermanentLicense":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtoaddapermanentlicense","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToAddAPermanentLicense","title":"How to Add a Permanent License","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sell a lifetime entitlement alongside a subscription and surface both flags through the paywall plugin."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"abstract":[{"text":"Attach the ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view modifiers from ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to a root view, driven by ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"title":"How to Present the UI","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/MockRevenueCatPaywallService":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"text":" conformer for previews and tests with a controllable entitlement stream.","type":"text"}],"title":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/mockrevenuecatpaywallservice","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"topic"}}}